Stay at home
Only go outside for food, health reasons or work (but only if you cannot work from home)
If you go out, stay 2 metres (6ft) away from other people at all times
Wash your hands as soon as you get home
Do not meet others, even friends or family.
You can spread the virus even if you donâ€™t have symptoms.

There are a limited number of seats available on an Air Cairo flight departing from Cairo to London Heathrow on Thursday 16 April. Bookings can be made on the Air Cairo website.
The Egyptian authorities announced on 16 March that scheduled flights into and out of the country would be suspended from 19 March until 31 March. The suspension was later extended to 15 April; it may be extended further.
This advice will continue to be updated with the latest information on returning to the UK.
If you have questions about visa requirements to enter the UK, please visit the GOV.UK website.
British nationals in Egypt should continue to regularly check this travel advice, and follow the instructions of the local authorities.
If you need urgent consular assistance, you can contact the Embassy on 02 2791 6000.
You can also follow the British Embassy in Cairo on Facebook and on Twitter.
Further information
See additional advice on making travel plans to return to the UK, or what to do if you cannot depart immediately.
